      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777281972491,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "if we will give lets say credentials of Instagram to our LLM, and we will say login to \nmy account and do 1 post. can this LLM model do this by their own -> No\nit doesn't have database access due to we can access database via code running and we know LLM\ncan't run the code.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "if we will give lets say credentials of Instagram to our LLM, and we will say login to \nmy account and do 1 post. can this LLM model do this by their own -> No\nit doesn't have database access due to we can access database via code running and we know LLM\ncan't run the code.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "3LBwVOqSjWfq6OEM4qVf8",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1395.5079902088494,
      "y": 70847.7570295378,
      "width": 1089,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
